WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.600
In this third video, we're going to polish up our Quarto dashboard and we're going to

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:10.020
talk a little bit about theming and styling.

00:00:10.020 --> 00:00:11.900
So let's start with theming.

00:00:11.900 --> 00:00:17.000
Quarto dashboards can be styled with one of the 25 themes from the Bootswatch project.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.620
So here, for example, I've used a theme.

00:00:19.620 --> 00:00:24.879
It's a theme I like to use for testing, just to make sure that I have the right syntax

00:00:24.879 --> 00:00:28.700
because it looks a little crazy, in my opinion, something like this.

00:00:28.700 --> 00:00:32.900
It's very fancy, but it is great for testing your code.

00:00:32.900 --> 00:00:35.919
You can really see when it actually takes effect.

00:00:35.919 --> 00:00:40.320
So we're setting theme equal to, in this case, the name of the theme is Quartz, and we're

00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:42.720
doing that under dashboard, as you can see.

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:46.000
So that's a little bit indented on the YAML.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:51.259
You can take a look at the various themes from this project.

00:00:51.259 --> 00:00:56.880
If you are familiar with any sort of web design, these are probably themes that are very familiar

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:57.919
to you.

00:00:57.919 --> 00:01:02.799
You may have used them in other Quarto things, like if you're making a website or if you're

00:01:02.799 --> 00:01:04.779
making slides.

00:01:04.779 --> 00:01:09.300
And otherwise, even if this is the first dashboard you're making and you haven't done any sort

00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:14.199
of theming work in another project, chances are you'll recognize some of these themes

00:01:14.199 --> 00:01:17.720
from websites you peruse.

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:22.739
We can also add a light and dark mode, and the way we do that in Quarto dashboards is

00:01:22.739 --> 00:01:26.959
very similar to how we do it in Quarto websites as well.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:33.879
So instead of setting a single theme, we then add a light and a dark option for our theme.

00:01:33.879 --> 00:01:39.120
And in general, I recommend choosing themes that pair nicely with each other.

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:42.820
So flatly and darkly, for example, pair nicely.

00:01:42.820 --> 00:01:47.779
And you can see here in this screenshot, it's a little tiny, but we've gained a little toggle

00:01:47.779 --> 00:01:51.160
button in our dashboard.

00:01:51.160 --> 00:01:56.080
The theme has also changed to flatly for the light version.

00:01:56.199 --> 00:02:02.519
And then when I toggle that switch, we go to darkly, so a dark background for this.

00:02:02.519 --> 00:02:07.199
Now obviously, if you're going to do this, it makes sense to take care to update your

00:02:07.199 --> 00:02:09.240
plots to go along with it as well.

00:02:09.240 --> 00:02:13.880
But for now, we're just going to focus on the theme aspect of things.

00:02:13.880 --> 00:02:15.559
We can also customize themes.

00:02:15.559 --> 00:02:20.880
So you can create an entirely custom theme and apply it to your dashboard as well.

00:02:20.880 --> 00:02:24.880
For that, you would write an SCSS file and simply pull that in.

00:02:24.880 --> 00:02:28.039
Or you can customize an existing boot swatch theme.

00:02:28.039 --> 00:02:32.399
So you could take an existing theme and say, there's just one thing I don't like about it,

00:02:32.399 --> 00:02:38.960
or a handful of things I'd like to customize further about it, and then bring those in

00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:43.600
by adding a custom SCSS file.

00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:53.440
So here, for example, we have a custom light SCSS file that we have loaded as our theme.

00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:59.639
And the way it's affecting things is in here, we can see that we've changed the font.

00:02:59.639 --> 00:03:02.600
So that's going to affect our output.

00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:08.039
We've also changed the background and foreground for our navigation bar.

00:03:08.039 --> 00:03:13.720
And we've also changed for the headers of our cards what the background should be and

00:03:13.720 --> 00:03:15.600
the text color should be.

00:03:15.600 --> 00:03:17.960
So those are all reflected here.

00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:22.800
As we can see, you're seeing that gold or bronze-ish headers, for example,

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:29.080
for your card titles with white text in front of them.

00:03:29.080 --> 00:03:31.919
All right.

00:03:31.919 --> 00:03:38.800
Here, we're using that same style file, but we're applying it to an existing theme,

00:03:38.800 --> 00:03:40.960
so to the sandstone theme.

00:03:40.960 --> 00:03:46.119
So you can see that the colors that are used for the value boxes, we're using colors like

00:03:46.119 --> 00:03:51.279
primary and secondary for those, have been updated as well.

00:03:51.279 --> 00:03:55.880
And then our custom theme has been layered on top of that.

00:03:55.880 --> 00:04:02.919
In general, when you're at the stage of polishing your dashboard, you're going to want a unified

00:04:02.919 --> 00:04:07.559
look for your dashboard, which is going to require customizing your dashboard along

00:04:07.559 --> 00:04:09.199
with your plots and tables.

00:04:09.199 --> 00:04:13.160
So you should be choosing colors that are complementary and visually appealing,

00:04:13.160 --> 00:04:17.519
at least to you, but also following accessibility best practices as well.

00:04:17.519 --> 00:04:22.079
So stick to predefined accessible color scales where possible.

00:04:22.079 --> 00:04:27.920
If you want to learn more about theming corto, I invite you to browse the documentation.

00:04:27.920 --> 00:04:32.440
So under Guide, Dashboards, and Using Dashboards, there is a theming page,

00:04:32.440 --> 00:04:38.760
and there is plenty of information there going into detail of how you can build your

00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:43.200
custom theme, all the SAS variables that you can use in order to do that.

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:49.119
We're going to dip our toes a little bit into this in this video and create custom-style

00:04:49.119 --> 00:04:55.279
dashboards, or actually take our Olympic dashboard and add a little bit of customization to it.

